I have a problem accessing the EventToCommand in my WPF4 application. It seems it is not accessible from the namespace I included.<br />
<br />
I added the references by using NUGET.<br />
<br />
The references GalaSoft.MvvmLight.Extras.WPF4, GalaSoft.MvvmLight.WPF4 and System.Windows.Interactivity were added.<br />
<br />
In my .xaml I included <br />
<pre><code>xmlns:cmd=&quot;namespace:GalaSoft.MvvmLight.Command;assembly=GalaSoft.MvvmLight.Extras.WPF4&quot;</code></pre>

I want to add a trigger to a textbox, something like:<br />
<pre><code>&lt;TextBlock Text=&quot;A command&quot; &gt;
  &lt;i:Interaction.Triggers&gt;
     &lt;i:EventTrigger EventName=&quot;MouseDown&quot;&gt;
        &lt;cmd:EventToCommand Command=&quot;{Binding DoActionCommand}&quot;/&gt;
     &lt;/i:EventTrigger&gt;
  &lt;/i:Interaction.Triggers&gt;
&lt;/TextBlock&gt;</code></pre>

However the EventToCommand is not recognized. (and I don't get IntelliSense from cmd:<br />
<br />
Can someone help?<br />
